# secrets — never commit credentials
.env
*.env
secrets/
**/kaggle.json

# Large data NOT needed by the hosted dashboard (must stay out of the repo):
#   - FIFA player CSV ~92 MB (availability degrades to a no-op without it)
#   - ESPN summary/scoreboard cache ~1.1 GB (re-fetched live at runtime)
# Everything else under data/ IS committed so the deployed app has its inputs
# (matches/features parquet, elo_ratings.json, models, results spine, shootouts).
data/raw/fifa_players/
data/raw/odds/
data/raw/thestatsapi/
data/raw/odds_feed/

# Tracker: COMMIT the settled ledger (the backfilled tournament record persists on
# the hosted site, which has an ephemeral filesystem). Open/pending tickets stay
# local — they accumulate live per-session on the site.
reports/clv_open.csv

